<TITLE> BFF to get ready asto-turf by November </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 2 (bdnews24.com)  Work on laying basement for the artificial football turf on the 'Balur Math' adjacent to the Bangladesh Football Federation will get underway by the middle of this month. Visiting FIFA development officer Mohshin Gilani told reporters on Saturday at BFF House after a meeting with the chairman of the women's football committee Sirajul Islam Bachchu. Gilani said that they had already appointed a local firm to lay the basement for the artificial turf and an international firm would lay the turf as soon as the completion of the foundation. He thinks Bangladesh will get the ready asto-turf by November this year. Meanwhile, AFC president Mohamed Bin Hamman unveiled the foundation stone of that artificial turf under the FIFA goal project-2 on March 29, 2008 and it is expected to cost $400,000 under the full supervision of football governing body. Gilani also presented a plan of women's football development as the BFF had been conducting a lot of activities for women's football in Bangladesh. bd
